<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
[[ 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4210616A-20C6-439C-B592-B4D7E6DC8E61" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura de Pinna 1988:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Listrura de Pinna</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="44" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4210616A-20C6-439C-B592-B4D7E6DC8E61" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura de Pinna 1988:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Listrura de Pinna</taxonomicName>
is the only genus of the subfamily Glanapteryginae occurring in small coastal rivers basins of southern and southeastern Brazil (de Pinna, 1988; Nico &amp; de Pinna, 1996; Landim &amp; Costa, 2002; de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki, 2002). All other glanapterygines (
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CE111DFD-61E6-413E-9C40-4FA94AF5E96B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Glanapteryx" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Glanapteryx Myers 1927:128" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glanapteryx Myers</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0185BBD-19F9-4041-97A0-2C199373D2E5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Typhlobelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Typhlobelus Myers 1944:593" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Typhlobelus Myers</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:46CFCD9F-784F-4509-AF61-3B0F13DA9B6D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Pygidianops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pygidianops Myers 1944:592" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pygidianops Myers</taxonomicName>
) are endemic to the Amazon and Orinoco river basins, northern South America (Myers, 1944; de Pinna, 1998; Costa &amp; Bockmann, 1994) and constitute a clade. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4210616A-20C6-439C-B592-B4D7E6DC8E61" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura de Pinna 1988:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Listrura</taxonomicName>
species inhabit interstitial spaces in the substrate (i. e., sand, litter) of shallow forest streams (Landim &amp; Costa, 2002; de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki, 2002). The genus includes four species: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="camposi">L. camposi (Miranda-Ribeiro)</taxonomicName>
, described from the rio Ribeira do Iguape basin, southern 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo State (Miranda-Ribeiro, 1957; de Pinna, 1988), and also found in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="ribeirão">ribeirao</normalizedToken>
da Ilha, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Florianópolis">Florianopolis</normalizedToken>
, Santa Catarina State (Nico &amp; de Pinna, 1996); 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:18634076-AB1F-449E-B96F-ED425752C81B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura nematopteryx de Pinna 1988:115" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nematopteryx">L. nematopteryx de Pinna</taxonomicName>
, known from two localities in river basins (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Iguaçû">Iguacu</normalizedToken>
and Estrela) adjacent to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="baía">baia</normalizedToken>
de Guanabara, Rio de Janeiro State (Miranda-Ribeiro, 1962; de Pinna, 1988); 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0E453A4-0003-40C8-806C-5B4DD82C62C0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura tetraradiata Landim &amp; Costa 2002:152" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tetraradiata">L. tetraradiata Landim &amp; Costa</taxonomicName>
, from the lagoa de Araruama system, Rio de Janeiro State, and considered the most basal species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4210616A-20C6-439C-B592-B4D7E6DC8E61" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura de Pinna 1988:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Listrura</taxonomicName>
(Landim &amp; Costa, 2002; de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki, 2002); and, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7F4797DE-1C17-4201-88CC-F7E22B1D7170" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura boticario de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki 2002:721" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boticario">L. boticario de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki</taxonomicName>
, from Salto Morato, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
State (de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki, 2002). In this paper we describe a new species from a coastal drainage in Picinguaba of northern 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo State, southeastern Brazil, previously misidentified as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:18634076-AB1F-449E-B96F-ED425752C81B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Listrura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Listrura nematopteryx de Pinna 1988:115" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nematopteryx">L. nematopteryx</taxonomicName>
(de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki, 2003).
</paragraph>
